<h2>Best activities to do in Shimla / Top things to do in Shimla</h2>

<h3>Toy Train Ride in Shimla</h3>
<p>Taking a trip on the Shimla Toy Train is one of the finest ways to relive your youth while seeing Himachal Pradesh's old-world charm. Book Shimla tour packages with invisit.</p>

<h3>Camping in Shimla</h3>
<p>Camping beneath the stars is one of the top things to do in Shimla for young people and couples. There are several campsites in and around Shimla, for an amazing camping and stargazing experience in Shimla.</p>


<h3>Trekking in Shimla</h3>
<p>Trekking is one of the top activities in Shimla. An early start is recommended for one-day hikes, although multi-day adventures can also be arranged through local organisations.</p>


<h3>Skiing in Shimla</h3>
<p>While in Shimla, explore Kufri, which is only 13 km from the main town and a prominent site for skiing in Shimla. The vistas and scenery here only improve, and the landscapes are more beautiful, undisturbed by the tourist influx.</p>


<h3>Handicrafts at Lakkar Bazar</h3>
<p>If you are at the Ridge, you must visit the nearby Lakkar Bazaar, which is one of Shimla's greatest shopping destinations. The street market is famous for its carved wooden toys and curiosities created by the local Sikh population.</p>



